<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 26 at 2:09PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Buckingham
County through 245 PM EDT...
At 209 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Wingina, or 11 miles northwest of Buckingham, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Wingina...
New Canton...
Centenary...
and Bremo Bluff.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
